object.script:
zoom = 0.5
function onTick() x = input.getNumber(10) y = input.getNumber(11) end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setMapColorOcean(20, 20, 20) screen.setMapColorShallows(30, 30, 30) screen.setMapColorLand(40, 40, 40) screen.setMapColorGrass(50, 50, 50) screen.setMapColorSand(60, 60, 60) screen.setMapColorSnow(240, 240, 240) screen.drawMap(x, y, zoom)
--screen dot screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, 150) screen.drawLine(14, 15, 17, 15) screen.drawLine(15, 14, 15, 17) end

function onTick()
heading=input.getNumber(1) RAIN=input.getNumber(2) WINDS=input.getNumber(3) WINDD=input.getNumber(4) HUMDITY=input.getNumber(5) X=input.getNumber(6) Y=input.getNumber(7) h1 = input.getBool(1) h2 = input.getBool(2) h3 = input.getBool(3) h4 = input.getBool(4) h5 = input.getBool(5) h6 = input.getBool(6) h7 = input.getBool(7) h8 = input.getBool(8) SND=input.getNumber(9) REC=input.getNumber(10)
end
function onDraw()
w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawClear() screen.setColor(255, 255, 255, 150) screen.drawTextBox(1, 90, w, 6, string.format("HEAD:%.0f", heading), -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 84, w, 6, "DIRC:", -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(45, 84, w, 6, string.format("XPOS:%.0f", X), -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(45, 90, w, 6, string.format("YPOS:%.0f", Y), -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(70, 72, w, 6, string.format("FQS:%.0f", SND), -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(70, 78, w, 6, string.format("FQR:%.0f", REC), -1, 0)
if h1 then screen.drawTextBox(27,84,w, 6,"ne", -1, 0) end
if h2 then screen.drawTextBox(27, 84,w, 6, "e", -1, 0) end
if h3 then screen.drawTextBox(27,84,w, 6,"se", -1, 0) end
if h4 then screen.drawTextBox(27, 84,w, 6, "s", -1, 0) end
if h5 then screen.drawTextBox(27,84,w, 6,"sw", -1, 0) end
if h6 then screen.drawTextBox(27, 84,w, 6, "w", -1, 0) end
if h7 then screen.drawTextBox(27,84,w, 6,"nw", -1, 0) end
if h8 then screen.drawTextBox(27,84,w, 6,"n", -1, 0) end
end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() value1 = input.getNumber(1) -- Read the first number from the script's composite input value2 = input.getNumber(2) -- Read the first number from the script's composite input value3 = input.getNumber(3) -- Read the first number from the script's composite inpuT value4 = input.getNumber(4) -- Read the first number from the script's composite input
end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) -- Set draw color to green screen.drawTextBox(1, 0, 30, 7, "RPS", -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 8, 30, 7, "WTS", -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 16, 30, 7, "BAT", -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 24, 30, 7, "SPD", -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 0, 30, 7, string.format("%.0f", value1), 1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 8, 30, 7, string.format("%.0f", value2), 1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 16, 30, 7, string.format("%.0f", value3), 1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 24, 30, 7, string.format("%.0f", value4), 1, 0) screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) screen.drawLine(0, 7, 32, 7) screen.drawLine(0, 15, 32, 15) screen.drawLine(0, 23, 32, 23)
end

function onTick() inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1) STPRESS = input.getBool(22) STPRESS2 = input.getBool(23)
NEXTSCREEN = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 17, 24, 14, 6) PREVSCREEN = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 24, 14, 6) DK = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 16, 14, 6) NV = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 17, 16, 14, 6) MG = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 8, 14, 6) SP = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 17, 8, 14, 6) WN = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 0, 14, 6) ST = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 17, 0, 14, 6)
output.setBool(1, NEXTSCREEN) output.setBool(2, PREVSCREEN) output.setBool(3, DK) output.setBool(4, NV) output.setBool(5, MG) output.setBool(6, SP) output.setBool(7, WN) output.setBool(20, ST) end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() --NEXT/PREV SCREEN BUTTON screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawRectF(1, 24, 14, 6) screen.drawRectF(17, 24, 14, 6) screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) screen.drawRect(1, 24, 14, 6) screen.drawRect(17, 24, 14, 6) screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(19, 25, 14, 6, ">", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 25, 14, 6, "<", 0, 0) --FIRST SET BUTTONS
screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawRectF(1, 16, 14, 6) screen.drawRectF(17, 16, 14, 6)
screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) screen.drawRect(1, 16, 14, 6) screen.drawRect(17, 16, 14, 6) screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(19, 17, 14, 6, "NV", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 17, 14, 6, "DK", 0, 0) --SECOND SET BUTTONS
screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawRectF(1, 8, 14, 6) screen.drawRectF(17, 8, 14, 6)
screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) screen.drawRect(1, 8, 14, 6) screen.drawRect(17, 8, 14, 6) screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(19, 9, 14, 6, "SP", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 9, 14, 6, "MG", 0, 0) --THRID SET BUTTONS
screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) screen.drawRectF(1, 0, 14, 6)
screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawRectF(17, 0, 14, 6)
if STPRESS then screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawRectF(17, 0, 14, 6) else screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawRectF(17, 0, 14, 6) end if STPRESS2 then screen.setColor(255, 165, 0) screen.drawRectF(17, 0, 14, 6) end screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) screen.drawRect(1, 0, 14, 6) screen.drawRect(17, 0, 14, 6) screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(19, 1, 14, 6, "ST", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 1, 14, 6, "WN", 0, 0)
end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() COUNTER = input.getNumber(1) -- Read the first number from the script's composite input end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) -- Set draw color to green screen.drawTextBox(0, (h/2)-10, w, 6, "LOADNG", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(0, (h/2)-4, w, 6, "MENU", 0, 0) screen.drawRect(1, (h/2)+2, 29, 5) screen.drawRectF(1,(h/2)+2, COUNTER, 5) end

function onTick() -- Example that adds two composite channels together and outputs the result inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1)
isPressingRectangleX = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 21, 0, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle1 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 8, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle2 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 11, 8, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle3 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 21, 8, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle4 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 16, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle5 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 11, 16, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle6 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 21, 16, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle7 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 1, 24, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle8 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 11, 24, 10, 8) isPressingRectangle9 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 21, 24, 10, 8)
if isPressingRectangleX then var = 0 else var = 0 end if isPressingRectangle1 then var = 1 end if isPressingRectangle2 then var = 2 end if isPressingRectangle3 then var = 3 end if isPressingRectangle4 then var = 4 end if isPressingRectangle5 then var = 5 end if isPressingRectangle6 then var = 6 end if isPressingRectangle7 then var = 7 end if isPressingRectangle8 then var = 8 end if isPressingRectangle9 then var = 9 end
output.setNumber(10, var)
end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() -- Example that draws a red circle in the center of the screen with a radius of 20 pixels W = screen.getWidth() H = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(255, 255, 255)
screen.drawRect(1, 0, 20, 8) --NUM screen.drawRect(21, 0, 10, 8) --X
screen.drawRect(1, 8, 10, 8) --1 screen.drawRect(1, 16, 10, 8) --4 screen.drawRect(1, 24, 10, 8) --7
screen.drawRect(11, 8, 10, 8) --2 screen.drawRect(11, 16, 10, 8) --5 screen.drawRect(11, 24, 10, 8) --8
screen.drawRect(21, 8, 10, 8) --3 screen.drawRect(21, 16, 10, 8) --6 screen.drawRect(21, 24, 10, 8) --9
screen.drawTextBox(1, 1, 20, 8, "F"..var, 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(21, 1, 10, 8, "X", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 9, 10, 8, "1", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 17, 10, 8, "4", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(1, 25, 10, 8, "7", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(11, 9, 10, 8, "2", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(11, 17, 10, 8, "5", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(11, 25, 10, 8, "8", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(21, 9, 10, 8, "3", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(21, 17, 10, 8, "6", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(21, 25, 10, 8, "9", 0, 0)
end
